# Copilot instructions — {{ ip }} verification environment

This repository area is a UVM verification environment for the IP
**{{ ip }}** (DUT module `{{ dut.module }}`), generated by uvm-gen
{{ gen_version }} for **Cadence Xcelium only** (single-step `xrun`, bundled
UVM-1.2, `-uvmhome CDNS-1.2`). Work happens in the phase order defined by
`.github/prompts/*.prompt.md`; each prompt states its precondition and its
definition of done.

## Directory layout

```
{{ ip }}_verif/
├─ cfg/                  # one YAML per IP configuration ('extends:' supported)
├─ agents/<name>_agent/  # custom interface agents (if/seq_item/driver/monitor/...)
├─ vip/<name>_vip/       # Cadence VIP wrappers (TODO(vip) markers)
├─ env/                  # {{ ip }}_env_cfg, {{ ip }}_env, scoreboard, coverage, vsequencer, RAL
├─ seq_lib/              # virtual sequences
├─ tests/                # {{ ip }}_base_test, {{ ip }}_smoke_test, ...
├─ tb/                   # {{ ip }}_tb_top (+ DUT stub)
├─ sim/                  # Makefile, tb.f, vip_*.f, {{ vsif_name }}, scripts/
{% if dv_scaffold %}
├─ docs/                 # CLAUDE.md (per-IP context — read before working), vplan.md
├─ dv/                   # methodology tree: tests/negative/ (chkq kit), lists/, cov/, status/
{% endif %}
└─ verif_matrix.yaml     # per-run verification tracking (auto-appended)
```

## Ground rules (violations break vertical reuse — do not bend them)

1. **Naming**: every class/package/file is prefixed `{{ ip }}_`. Keep it that
   way for anything you add.
2. **One config object**: `{{ ip }}_env_cfg` (env/{{ ip }}_env_cfg.sv) is the
   ONLY external contract of the env. It carries all sub-configs, all virtual
   interfaces, and the RAL knobs, and is retrieved via
   `uvm_config_db#({{ ip }}_env_cfg)::get(this, "", "cfg", cfg)` in the env.
   Never fetch a virtual interface from the config_db inside an agent or env
   component, and never reference `{{ ip }}_tb_top` (or any absolute
   hierarchy) from `agents/`, `vip/`, `env/`, or `seq_lib/` code.
3. **is_active**: each agent/VIP has an `is_active` switch in its sub-config.
   Passive agents must not construct drivers/sequencers (the generated agents
   already behave this way — preserve it). Virtual sequences null-check
   sequencer handles so the same test runs when an SoC flips everything
   passive: `+{{ IP }}_PASSIVE=all`.
4. **Multi-config**: one YAML per configuration in `cfg/`, each with a
   `config_name` and a `params:` map; shared spec lives in a base YAML via
   `extends:` (deep-merge, config file wins). Configs are selected at run
   time with `CFG=cfg/<file>.yaml` — never hardcode parameter values in SV;
   read them from `{{ ip }}_env_cfg` (params map / typed mirrors).
5. **Never-overwrite generator**: re-running uvm-gen only creates files that
   do not exist. Do not regenerate with `--force` to "fix" a file — edit it.
6. **Xcelium only**: do not add flags/constructs for other simulators.

## Commands (exact, run from `sim/`)

```bash
make compile                                        # compile + elaborate sanity
make run TEST={{ ip }}_smoke_test                   # single run (SEED=<n|random>)
make run TEST=<test> CFG=cfg/<config>.yaml          # run under a configuration
make waves TEST=<test>                              # -access +rwc + SHM probing
make regress                                        # vmanager -execcmd "launch {{ vsif_name }}"
make matrix                                         # config vs. status from ../verif_matrix.yaml
make clean
```

* Logs land in `sim/results/<config_name>/<test>_seed<seed>.log`.
* Every `make run` appends a record (config, param hash, test, seed,
  pass/fail, git rev, coverage when available) to `verif_matrix.yaml`.
* Every simulation prints a `CFG_BANNER` configuration signature — quote it
  when reporting results.
* Cadence VIPs: `$CDN_VIP_ROOT` must be set when the active config lists
  `vips:`; the per-protocol compile filelist is `sim/vip_<protocol>.f`.
* New tests: add the class under `tests/`, add an include line to
  `tests/{{ ip }}_test_pkg.sv`, and register a `test` entry in
  `sim/{{ vsif_name }}` (per-config vsif, session `{{ ip }}_<config_name>`).
{% if dv_scaffold %}
* Checker-qualification (chkq) tests are opt-in and out of the functional
  build: `make run TEST={{ ip }}_example_neg_test
  EXTRA_FILELISTS=${{ IP }}_VERIF_HOME/dv/tests/negative/chkq.f
  XRUN_OPTS='+CHKQ_ENABLE -access +rwc'`. Extend `{{ ip }}_chkq_base_test`,
  keep HDL paths in `dv/tests/negative/chkq_paths.svh`, register each in
  `dv/lists/chkq.list`. Functional tests must NEVER set `+CHKQ_ENABLE`.
* Read `docs/CLAUDE.md` before working on {{ ip }}; trace every test/bin/check
  to a `VP-{{ IP }}-xxx` row in `docs/vplan.md`; append coverage waivers to
  `dv/cov/exclusion_requests.md` (a human applies them).
{% endif %}

## Definition of done, per phase

| Phase | Prompt | Done when |
|---|---|---|
| 1. DUT connection | `connect-dut.prompt.md` | `make compile` clean with real RTL (no DUT stub note) |
| 2. Protocol agents | `implement-agents.prompt.md` | `make run TEST={{ ip }}_smoke_test` ends with UVM_ERROR 0 |
| 3. Tests | `write-tests.prompt.md` | new tests pass and are registered in the vsif |
| 4. Regression triage | `triage-regression.prompt.md` | every regression failure classified + fixed or ticketed |
| 5. Coverage closure | `coverage-closure.prompt.md` | coverage goals met per configuration |
| 6. Verification closure | `verif-closure.prompt.md` | `make matrix` CLEAN for every configuration; closure summary written |
